      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carle_Place%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "In 1946, William J. Levitt bought 19 acres near the station and built 600 low‑cost houses, sparking rapid growth.",
